&lt;p&gt;Awardco is reimagining the workplace to be more rewarding, supportive, and fun for everyone. As one of the fastest-growing companies in the employee experience industry, our mission is to help employees love what they do, love where they work, and get recognized for their efforts—especially our own employees! And as winners of Glassdoor’s Best Places to Work, Best in Brightest in the Nation, and Great Place to Work, we do much more than talk the talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an Application Security Engineer joining our IT &amp;amp; Security team to build and mature our application security program as we continue to scale our SaaS platform.&amp;nbsp;In this role, you’ll partner closely with product, engineering, and operations teams to design, build, and ship secure features — without slowing down creativity and innovation. You’ll own the secure software development lifecycle, lead security reviews for new capabilities, and help drive a culture where every engineer treats security as part of quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll also play a key role in enabling developers, building the skills and tooling they need to own security in their code through secure coding guidance, training, and a strong Security Champions program.&amp;nbsp;If you enjoy rolling up your sleeves, solving real-world security problems, and making cloud products safer by design, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embed security checkpoints into planning, design, development, testing, and release processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering leads to ensure new features ship with security built in, not bolted on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate threat modeling for new services, APIs, and integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend secure patterns and architectures for multi-tenant SaaS and cloud-native components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform targeted secure code reviews for high‑risk features and components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and tune SAST, DAST, dependency, and container scanning to reduce noise and highlight real risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate and optimize AI-assisted application security tools (e.g., GitHub Advanced Security, Snyk, Wiz, or similar) within developer workflows to improve signal and remediation speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define and maintain secure coding standards and patterns used across engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Triage, prioritize, and track remediation of application and API vulnerabilities across the stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on secure use of authentication, authorization, cryptography, and data protection controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help evaluate and integrate third‑party services and SDKs from a security perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, technical explanations of findings, mitigations, and residual risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and deliver pragmatic secure coding training tailored to our tech stack and common issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create playbooks, checklists, and self‑service guidance for developers to help them ship secure code independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion a “secure by default” mindset across product and engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow and enhance the Security Champions program, mentoring developers to act as local security advocates on their teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with investigation and remediation for application‑level security incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help improve detection, logging, and alerting for application and API misuse.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in application security or in software engineering with a strong security focus for web applications or APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands‑on experience securing cloud‑hosted, multi‑tenant SaaS applications on a major public cloud platform.&lt

&lt;p&gt;The Awardco Center of Excellence (COE) helps shape best practices in recognition, engagement, and employee experience through research, practical insight, and education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The COE Research and Insights Manager will support this work by designing and delivering high-quality research studies, helping translate findings into thought leadership content, and contributing to internal and external education efforts. This role is ideal for someone with a strong foundation in I/O psychology, employee research, and survey design who enjoys turning data into practical, usable insight.This is an individual contributor role focused on research execution, study delivery, benchmark development, and content support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Design and Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, field, and manage original COE research studies focused on topics such as employee engagement, recognition, motivation, wellbeing, and workplace experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development of surveys, questionnaires, benchmarks, and measurement frameworks that can be used across COE initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain high standards for study quality, methodology, interpretation, and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal stakeholders to align research priorities to COE content and insight needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thought Leadership and Insight Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate research findings into practical thought leadership assets including reports, white papers, articles, presentations, and supporting materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of a recognizable Awardco point of view on employee recognition and engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support external-facing research storytelling through digestible, practitioner-friendly outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Enablement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help design and deliver webinars, workshops, internal learning sessions, and training materials grounded in research findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn complex organizational psychology concepts into clear, useful education for HR and EX practitioner audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the COE in building repeatable research-based materials that can be used across events, content, and enablement efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s degree in Industrial-Organizational Psychology, Organizational Psychology, Applied Psychology, Behavioral Science, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-7 years of experience in employee research, survey design, people science, organizational research, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience designing and delivering research studies end-to-end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and written communication skills, with the ability to turn findings into practical recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with survey platforms, research methods, and data storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable presenting findings to internal stakeholders and professional audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience contributing to thought leadership, research publications, or educational content is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong grounding in I/O or people science principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to balance methodological rigor with business practicality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curious, collaborative, and comfortable working across functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excited by building research that informs content, education, and market perspective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
